      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2015-05-19T19:47:59Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <updateDate>2015-04-28T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <actionDate>2015-04-28</actionDate>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>This bill authorizes the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission (FERC), upon the request of the licensee for the project numbered 12478-003 (Gibson Dam, Montana), to extend for six years the time period during which the licensee is required to commence construction.</p> <p>Commences such time period upon expiration of the previous extension issued by FERC before enactment of this Act. </p>]]></text>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
        </item>
        <item>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2016-04-07T16:38:45Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <updateDate>2016-03-15T12:30:47Z</updateDate>
          <actionDate>2016-03-15</actionDate>
          <versionCode>81</versionCode>
          <actionDesc>Passed House without amendment</actionDesc>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>(This measure has not been amended since it was introduced. The summary has been expanded because action occurred on the measure.)</p> <p>(Sec. 1) This bill authorizes the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission to extend by six years the time period during which Gibson Dam Hydroelectric Company is required to commence construction on the Gibson Dam Hydroelectric Project located on the Sun River in Lewis, Clark, and Teton Counties, Montana.</p> <p>The six-year time period starts upon expiration of the last extension.</p> <p><br> </p>]]></text>
          <name>Passed House without amendment</name>
        </item>
